    "body": "That sounds like a great mod but that is not something that we can support by default because it breaks credible neutrality and there is no oracle system that cannot be manipulated. All oracle systems have too strong of trust assumptions to enshrine into the op stack at this time.\r\n\r\nFollow up questions: What is the security model around chainlink's vwap? What prices does it report on?",
